name: garage construction, wood, non-insulated, fire-protected | garage, wood, non-insulated, fire-protected | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/15622/documentation

This global dataset is a copy of the regional CH dataset, except for the following modifications.;The production volume represents the global annual production.;The geographicalCorrelation score of every pedigree matrix of was changed to '5'.;The comments below were part of the CH regional dataset.;This dataset represents the construction of 1 m2 of a wooden garage as typically used in farms for the storage of machinery. Features of the model: Building volume: 630 m3; Useable space: 111 m2; Service life span: 50 years.;The garage comprises of a ceiling with non-flammable material and is not insulated. It is a simple construction of wooden walls without insulation material as required for parking vehicles with combustion engine; light basement with concrete. ;The repair percentage and the depreciation period of individual construction elements come from Agroscope Tanikon’s Modular Construction Standards for Farm Building Costs (Hilty & Herzog 2000). The construction variants were compiled by D. Herzog, Agroscope Tanikon. ;This dataset refers to an average situation; for specific situations exchanges might differ substantially due to site specific parameters.

The activity starts with the construction of the building.

Elements included are: Closed garage, concrete floor, non insulated wood construction, flame-resistant; not included are: non-flame-resistant part of the shed
The activity ends with the disposal of the building material, i.e. brick, bulk iron, concrete, plastics, and waste wood.
category: F:Construction/41:Construction of buildings/410:Construction of buildings/4100:Construction of buildings

processDocumentation.technologyDescription: The calculation of the construction materials employed is based on Agroscope PBK+  (Modular Construction Standards for Farm Building Costs +) System (Dux 2004). Based on construction variants for model buildings, the necessary building materials for construction, repair and replacement are calculated with the aid of the PBK+ database. In addition, the consumption of energy and auxiliary materials during operation of the building can be determined.
processDocumentation.dataTreatmentDescription: The amount of the exchanges are copy from a regional dataset.
processDocumentation.samplingDescription:
Features of the model used: Building volume: 630 m3; Useable space: 111 m2; Service life span: 50 years.
The repair percentage and the depreciation period of individual construction elements come from ART Tanikon’s Modular Construction Standards for Farm Building Costs (Hilty & Herzog 2000). The construction variants were compiled by D. Herzog, ART Tanikon.
